<h3 align=center>Game Tab</h3>
<p>The Game Options tab allows you to set up the game options and/or chat with other players
before the game actually starts.  The game host may configure game and player options,
as needed.
Players may configure their individual options as needed.  When everyone is ready, the host may
start the game.</p>

<p>The upper portion of the game tab contains the game <a href="Chat.html#_RefChatWindow">chat window</a>
and the game <a href="Chat.html#_RefUserList">user list</a>.  The lower portion consists of tabs
for the game/player Options, as well as additional Chat tabs.</p>  

<h4><a name="_RefSetup">Setting Up The Game</a></h4>
<p>Before a game can be started by the host, it must be set up--this includes the host setting all
game and player options, and other players setting their own options (if any).  Most options will have
default values and will not need to be set directly.  Once all options are set, each player, other
than the host, must select <i>Ready</i> by clicking the button on the upper portion of the game tab.
Once all players are ready, the host may click <i>Start Game</i> (also located on the upper portion
of the game tab).</p>

<p>Note that players who are ready will have the <a href="Icons.html">Ready Icon</a> displayed next
to their names in the <a href="#_RefGameChat">game user list</a>.  The host's <i>Start Game</i> button
will be disabled until all players are ready.  Players may also click the <i>Ready</i> button again
to mark themselves as unready and thus prevent the host from starting the game.</p>

<p>The host may ban a troublesome player (like one who won't click ready) at any time by selecting
the user's name in the <a href="#_RefGameChat">game user list</a> and clicking the <i>Ban</i> button
(located at the bottom of the game user list).  This will eject the user from the game and prevent
them from returning.</p>

<p>Any player may leave the game at any time before it is started by the host by selecting the
<i>Leave Game</i> button (located on the upper portion of the game tab).  The host may
dissolve the
game at any time before it is started by selecting the <i>Dissolve Game</i> button (also located on
the upper portion of the game tab).</p>

