<h4><a name="_RefGameChat">Game Chat and User List</a></h4>
<p>All chat in the game <a href="Chat.html#_RefChatWindow">chat window</a> will be delivered to all
players in the game (unless whispered).  The game <a href="Chat.html#_RefUserList">user list</a>
supports some additional features over a normal user list: the game host has the
<a href="Icons.html">Captain icon</a> next to username and is always displayed at the top of the
list.  Each player in the game list (other than the host), displays their ping to the game host to
the right of their name.</p>

If you are the game host and have chosen the <i>Ask To Join</i>
<a href="EntryRestrictions.html">entry restriction</a>, then a message will appear in your game chat
window whenever a user wishes to join your game.  You can click on <i>accept</i> or <i>reject</i> in
the message to allow the user to join or dismiss them.

<p><a href="#_RefTop">Return to Top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_RefTeamChat">Team Chat</a></h4>
<p>The Team Chat tab allows you to <a href="Chat.html">chat</a> between members of your team (if any).&nbsp;
All chat on this tab goes only to you and your team members (excluding whispers).  Note that there
is no separate User list for the Team Chat tab.</p>

<p><a href="#_RefTop">Return to Top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_RefLobbyChat">Lobby Chat</a></h4>
<p>The Lobby Chat tab allows you to <a href="Chat.html">chat</a> with users in your current
Lobby/room.
All chat on this tab goes to all users in your Lobby room (excluding whispers).  You can use this tab
to ask other users to come join your game or to just to chat with others as you wait for your game
to begin.</p>

